HEADWORD: Pentalpha
<hw>Pen*tal"pha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/: cf. F. <ets>pentalpha</ets>. See <er>Penta-</er>, and
